sql:
SELECT med_code, description
FROM med_codes
WHERE is_active = 1 AND disease_id = 1;

SELECT patient_id, date_recorded
FROM patient_med_codes
WHERE med_code_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Healing journey" refers to the period a patient is undergoing medical treatments;
- "Ongoing treatments" are treatments that have started but have not yet been marked as completed (i.e., no end date);
- The query considers all patients who have at least one treatment without an end date.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_read_code_count
FROM read_codes
WHERE disease_id = 1 AND is_active = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_med_code_count
  FROM med_codes
  WHERE is_active = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "healers" refers to healthcare professionals;
- "tended to more than one patient" means the healthcare professionals have administered more than one treatment;
- "from the start to the end of their treatments" refers to the duration between the start date and the end date of the treatments.

- "Top three" refers to the highest counts of diagnoses for each healthcare professional;
- "Common diseases" are those that are diagnosed most frequently;
- "Diagnosed by each healthcare professional" means the results are specific to each healthcare professional.

